Key findings:
- HSPAN achieves 35.7673 dB average PSNR on medical images
- ~7.18% improvement over bicubic baseline (PSNR)
- Strong improvement in structural similarity (SSIM +0.0254)
- Significant gain observed in difficult images (e.g., img007)

================================================================================
4. CONCLUSION
================================================================================
This project successfully achieved both objectives:

1. Core work: Implemented HSPAN and validated performance on benchmark datasets
2. Extension: Applied the pretrained model to medical image enhancement

The extension demonstrates that attention-based SR models trained on natural images 
can generalize effectively to medical-style data without retraining. Quantitative 
results show consistent and significant improvements over bicubic interpolation.

This implementation serves as a research prototype for academic purposes.

Limitations:
- Evaluation performed on only 10 images
- No domain-specific training on medical datasets

Future work:
- Train and fine-tune on large-scale medical datasets
- Incorporate domain-specific priors
- Evaluate on real clinical data (e.g., DICOM scans)
- Optimize model for real-time healthcare deployment
